--- Part 5: Key pattern ---
  delta(b3) = 0 for ALL bad vertices? True
  This means: adding vertex v adds EQUAL amounts to ker(d3) and rank(d4)
  delta_ker = delta_rank_d4 exactly
  The 'new' kernel directions from v-paths are FULLY saturated by 'new' d4 boundaries
  The ORIGINAL T\v cycle survives because it's orthogonal to the new content

  For i_*-injectivity: the embedded T\v cycle is NOT in im(d_4^T)
  This means: im(d_4^T) = im(d_4^{T\v}) + (v-paths contribution)
  And: the v-paths contribution is disjoint from the T\v cycle space

DONE.
